title: Weather Stations, West Virginia
name: Weather Stations, West Virginia
description:
Cooperative weather stations operated by local observers which generally report max/min temperatures and precipitation. National Weather Service (NWS) data are also included in this dataset. Custodian of climate data is the National Climate Data Center (NCDC), the world's largest active archive of weather data. Currentness: Historical cooperative station index through 1999.

Shapefile downloaded from West Virginia GIS Technical Center and uploaded into Geocommons as shp, dbf, and shx.
